    "narrative": "Today\u2019s optimal lineup for Ghost Ride the WHIP leans heavily on favorable matchups against vulnerable arms to drive our category performance. The cornerstone of the day is **James Wood**, who commands the highest score at 75.94. batting lead-off against McGreevy; his combination of order-dependent plate appearances and a favorable park factor makes him our safest bet for runs and immediate base-path pressure. Alongside him, **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (75.73) provide the elite speed profile we prioritize. **Mickey Moniak** benefits significantly from a massive 14% park boost and a strong platoon edge against Javier, while **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** capitalizes on a high-upside matchup against Severino, where his ability to steal bags outweighs the minor risk of the catcher\u2019s pop time.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the morning involved **Austin Riley**, whose 44.64 projection ultimately fell short of our active threshold. While **Austin Riley** carries a high base skill, the matchup against Detmers (xERA 3.06) effectively neutralized his upside, making him a riskier start compared to the volume efficiency provided by **Tyler Soderstrom** or **Trevor Story**. **Trevor Story** remains a high-variance play; despite a 5% wind-in penalty, his encounter with the volatile Drohan (xERA 10.13) gives him the statistical ceiling necessary to earn the utility spot. We are monitoring the weather closely, as the wind-in factor could suppress fly-ball power, but the pitching matchup remains too favorable to bench him.\n\nRounding out the bottom of the order, **Kyle Karros** (55.17) and **Zach McKinstry** (49.66) offer marginal efficiency. **Kyle Karros** benefits from a strong park factor and SP matchup, though his position in the 9-hole limits his R/RBI floor. We continue to hold **Josh Naylor** and **Jose Caballero** on the bench today, as they are not currently featured in their respective team\u2019s starting lineups. We will remain vigilant for defensive replacements or late-game pinch-hit scenarios to ensure our remaining bench depth\u2014including **Seiya Suzuki**, **Brice Turang**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Alex Freeland**, **Carson Williams**, **Gabriel Arias**, and **Travis Bazzana**\u2014is ready to be deployed should the situation necessitate a pivot.",
